<br>
*  One is that these events are a good way for people to learn raiding skills.  The old planes are a bit more forgiving of folks than, say, the Halls of Testing or even the plate cycle in Kael.  This is assuming, of course, you have experienced pullers available.  You certainly learn good tactics on dragon raids (resists, waves, timing the nuke down, etc...), but it doesn't really prepare you for higher end zone-raids.<br>
<br>
*  Another is that they are not level limited.  The old world dragons are great fun still, but the level cap eliminates a large number of FV inhabitants.<br>
<br>
*  Finally, despite the ensuing expansions, the old planes still have a good deal of fairly decent items, especially for the type of folks who will end up on an open raid (assuming here that guilded folks who can raid these places with their guilds will step back and let the unguilded/small guilds fill the slots).  It is no where near top of the line, but still useful.  And the rate of drops one gets in a full clearing means more people go home with something, even a crappy drop, than on a dragon raid.<br>
<br>
BUT, I think if you are going to do plane raids in this format, you need to be pretty cutthroat about raid size, and discipline.  Raids above 24 people are both overkill and unwieldy.  People show up late, or are disruptive, need to be bounced.<br>
<br>
Anyway, some random thoughts.  Great idea, and I hope you guys keep it going! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gardon1076>Gardon1076</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/10/03 2:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=399.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> d</span><hr size=1> Fear would be nice. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=maxvs>Maxvs</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/10/03 3:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=399.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: d</span><hr size=1> Hate <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=maeroth>Maeroth</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/10/03 3:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=399.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: d</span><hr size=1> Fear! I'd like to see Fear! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END